<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-1450] Memtable flush causes bad &quot;reversed&quot; get_slice</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1450</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If columns are inserted into a row before and after a memtable flush, a get_slice() after the flush with reversed=True will return incorrect results.  See attached patch to reproduce.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Cassandra Trunk&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
        <key id="12472952">CASSANDRA-1450</key>
